														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2366158">
									

<p>I believe the way it works is that Wondertainments have existed since ye olden days of the Djoricverse, and are basically the physical manifestations of humanity's creativity (although they probably went under a different label before Reginald came up with the name), teaching cavemen the secret of fire (see AiC) and otherwise guiding along humanity with their insights. People who fit the role of a Wondertainment would be granted all the powers and privileges that a Wondertainment possessed (although the selection process evidently isn't flawless, as shown by Reginald here joining the Factory, which is pretty much the antithesis of Wondertainment and everything they stand for.) However, no Wondertainment thus far has managed to unlocked their true potential; how that is done, what advantages come with that, and other such details I leave for Djoric to explore in the future.<br />
Feel free to correct me if I'm wrong, as always.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>And if the whole world is crashing down&#8230; fall through space out of mind with me.</p>

