			<div class="content" id="post-content-2366171">
									

<p>Sorta close.</p>
<p>Every sapient being has the potential to be Wondertainment. Most who show up are on the low end of the spectrum, and thus while wonderful, don't do much anomalous at all. Their form of magic is rather mundane.</p>
<p>But then you get people like Reggie, who have The Stuff. Now, everyone has a little bit of The Stuff. It's like Spiral Power. Erryone has it, but some people <em>have it</em>, you know? This is where things get magical.</p>
<p>As far as the title of Wondertainment is concerned, the number and spread is uncertain, mostly to allow for a certain fluidity of both character and timeline, so that other people can have valid Wondertainments. This is just for those individuals who claim the name, though, there are a great many who do not. 'Familial relations' of the Wondertainments are not genetic.</p>
<p>Weird Al is a Wondertainment. It is known.</p>

							</div>

								
					
