															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jj-pryer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1895483); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1895483&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251223" alt="JJ Pryer" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1895483)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jj-pryer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1895483); return false;" >JJ Pryer</a></span> <span class="odate time_1441691628 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Sep 2015 05:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2371691">
									

<p>Seems as though you could almost integrate a Santa Claus (and/or his elves) into the picture. A benevolent, jolly spirit who builds toys for children and gladly delivers them via impossible means. Either he can be a Wondertainment himself or a mascot or simply a deliverer of the stuff, if you wish to have him in this canon at all. Except, of course, he'd be a benevolent flavor of Wondertainment that wouldn't make such terrifying toys. (Personally, I prefer Santa when he isn't made into something creepy or scary.)</p>

							</div>

								
					
